author: Sihan Goi
text:
A pretty decent gym spread across the 3rd and 4th floors of a commercial building at the junction of Middle Road and another small lane.
3rd floor has cardio machines, cable machines, a few plate loaded machines, dumbbells up to 30kg, 2 power racks, a Smith machine, benches. 4th floor gets more serious with 6 power racks with attached platforms (but somehow only 5 barbells), a hex bar, a short bar, ez bar, fixed bars, benches, dumbbells up to 50kg, plate loaded machines, bumper plates and rubberized plates.
About the barbells, I remember seeing Eleiko bars advertised, but the 5 bars there were brandless hybrid bars with both PL and WL markings on a rather smooth knurl, so you may have grip issues if lifting heavy. Thankfully, all of them spin OK. Perhaps the Eleiko bars (if they have any) are kept during non staffed hours like some other clubs.

There is a sign at the corner platform that allows chalk usage only there, which is better than pretty much any other AF I've been to since they all disallow chalk usage. You do have up clean up after yourself but that's to be expected.

Went there around 7am on a Friday and trained until around 9am, crowd was also non existent. Not much to complain about equipment wise, except maybe a lack of warmup equipment such as foam rollers, bands, etc, or a space to warm up at. However, facilities wise, there are only 2 shower stalls per floor, and no space to change outside of the stall. I generally don't like to put on my clothes in the shower area since the floors are wet, but in this case there wasn't much choice.

author: T L
text:
I honestly don‚Äôt even know where to begin with how disgusted I am by the state of this this gym. I‚Äôve been a member for a while, but the recent months bathroom experience was so vile it might just be the last straw.

A wretched, persistent yellow substance is clearly visible on the toilet bowl. I can‚Äôt even begin to fathom how unsanitary that is. Who is responsible for cleaning this place, and why aren‚Äôt they doing their job? Apparently it seems that this has been going on for the last couple months. Unsure if they‚Äôre trying to cut costs by not hiring a cleaner for this outlet but it‚Äôs the worst decision management could make. Instead of letting your part time secondary school employees do the cleaning please hire a professional.

This gym had huge potential. Central location, easily accessible and one of the best lighting amongst other clubs with the purple lights. It‚Äôs a shame they had to compromise on hygiene and cleanliness. Floors were sticky and everywhere looked like it hasn‚Äôt been cleaned for a good amount of time.

For the sake of your own mental health (and physical health), do yourself a favor and avoid this gym unless you want to deal with an absolutely wretched bathroom experience. Until they deal with this, it‚Äôs best you look for somewhere else to go.

author: Hao Wu
text:
The Bugis anytime fitness gym has great equipment and friendly, helpful staff. I really enjoy working out here, the machines are well-maintained and there‚Äôs a good variety for all types of training.
However, the cleanliness of the showers and toilets needs serious improvement. They‚Äôre often dirty and not well-kept, which takes away from the overall experience.
Hope management can address this soon, as it would make the gym much more enjoyable for everyone.

author: Hafizh Shah
text:
‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê 5/5 ‚Äì Great Gym with a Welcoming Atmosphere

I‚Äôve been a member at Anytime Fitness for a while now, and it‚Äôs been an awesome experience. One of the best things about this gym is the convenience‚Äîbeing open 24/7 makes it incredibly easy to fit a workout into a busy schedule, no matter the time of day.

The facility is always clean, organized, and well-equipped with everything you need‚Äîwhether you're into weight training, cardio, or functional fitness. The equipment is modern and well-maintained, and I rarely have to wait to use anything.

What really makes this location stand out is the friendly and supportive staff. The team here is welcoming, knowledgeable, and always willing to help, whether you‚Äôre just getting started or need advice on leveling up your routine. They create a community vibe that makes working out more enjoyable and less intimidating.

There are also personal training options and group sessions if you want some extra motivation or structure in your workouts. I‚Äôve seen real progress since joining, and I feel stronger and more energized.

Highly recommend Anytime Fitness if you're looking for a clean, safe, and flexible gym with a great atmosphere!

I especially appreciate the variety of equipment and number of racks available, compared to other branches.

The only issue is it‚Äôs good location, which can cause it to be very crowded most of the time.

Haven‚Äôt had any encounters with the staff yet but I assume they are nice as per AF standard.

The best part? Cleanliness. The gym is spotless‚Äîfloors, mirrors, equipment, and locker rooms are always in great condition. Staff are friendly and quick to sanitize, and members seem to follow good hygiene practices too.

Found out my auto payment did not go through as my card was changed by the bank due to fraud transactions. Cancelled my subscription. It's okay, many competitors in the area who have more reasonable policies. Also, gym itself isn't that great anyway. Small and subpar equipment.

The facility is clean, well-maintained, and equipped with modern machines and free weights for both beginners and seasoned fitness enthusiasts. What makes this branch especially appealing is its friendly and helpful staff, who create a supportive atmosphere that motivates members to stay consistent with their fitness goals. Its central location in Bugis also makes it easy to drop in before or after work, school, or shopping.

It plays an extremely loud volume (audible over noise cancelling headphones). For the record, it is very easy to find a gym that music playing at a reasonable volume, and where the staff are polite and responsive to customer concernsm and don't send emails like this. That gym is not Anytime Bugis. While the facilities are fine, this attitude is the main reason I would not recommend this gym.

I generally don't write Google Reviews but I got an email from Anytime asking me to review them online after I terminated my membership. So, here it is, as requested.

text: The trainers' knowledge and commitment to assisting members in succeeding are incomparable. They are friendly, competent, and always willing to offer advice or respond to inquiries. You'll discover everything you need, no matter if you're a novice or an experienced athlete, to reach your fitness objectives. The gym is roomy, with two stories and, from what I've heard, a third on the way, providing enough space for a range of workouts. It is a five-star location considering the excellent facilities, superb lighting, and competent instructors.

author: Justinian Tabucanon
text:
I visited Singapore recently for a few days about 2 weeks ago. I wanted to have a decent work out in Singapore, because I know that I would be eating heaps of treats around the country.

I recently signed up for an Anytime fitness in Australia, and I was still on my 3rd week on my membership. So, as per my contract, this meant I couldn't go to any Anytime Fitness locations aside from the one I singed up for.

Before going on my trip, I asked my local Anytime Fitness whether it would be possible for me to go to Singapore and whether I would be able to train there for 2 days (not even a week, only a couple of sessions), since I didn't want to lose track of my fitness progress. My local gym advised me that it should be ok, since they would usually have people from other Australian States, and from overseas that have the same issue as me, but they would just let them train since they are still part of the community.

So, I went to Singapore, and I walked all the way to this branch (Bugis branch?), and I was denied access by the staff stating that they could not possibly accommodate my fitness needs since I am still within the one month clause of my contract. They didn't even offer a free one time session for that day.

It is frustrating as well because now, I couldn't pause my membership after the rejection.

It just hurts to know that this branch (and I hope this does not reflect the whole company/franchise) does not care as much about your fitness goals. I understand the law, and I know that they did it under their jurisdiction. But, from a customer service perspective, it is definitely a 1 star experience for me.

I thought it was both illogical and ridiculous that paying members of the gym have to pay that $60 fine even after verification that we are indeed members. I mean I get it if one of us were a guest‚Ä¶

Nothing technically wrong with the management‚Äôs decisions, but this inflexibility to stick to a ridiculous rule ‚Ä¶ not sure I would recommend more of my friends to join this gym.

Remember to always tap your key fob guys

author: Stevie Wander
text:
The location of this gym is already a win as it is between Suntec and Bugis, there is no shortage of good food for the post-workout bulk. If you need 800 calories char kway teow for dirty bulking just turn left upon exit and walk to Albert food centre.

There are 2 floors, level 3 and 4. Level 3 has more machines and threadmills, if you want to hit isolated muscle parts without free weights and run (Though running on concrete is generally much better).

Level 4 is where you see the Ronnie Coleman - ish lifters whom you will be proud to ask for help if you ever have a renovation and need some movers. There are cable machines, at least 8 benches, and 4 squat racks. Very spacious and less narrow than mall gyms.

You can access the gym using the lift or stairs, I prefer the stairs as I loveeeee legs day. Legs day are awesome, I like the feeling after great squats and deadlifts I walk down one step at a time. Don‚Äôt skip leg days (no really you will just look imbalance)

Anytime Bugis is a good choice for beginners or new year resolutioners who stop coming after a month. It has ample machines and free weights, just take note 6pm - 8.30pm on weekdays it is crowded. Weekends generally empty, and Monday is International Chest Day so good luck finding a bench or rack in the evening.

author: Neo Kung
text: Anytime Fitness near Bugis is open all the time, but not always crowded. I went on a weekday evening to register for a membership and happened to get a 20% discount, making it SGD 95 per month. However, you need to buy a key fob, which isn't cheap at SGD 85, but it grants access to branches worldwide, which is quite attractive. It has two floors, and you need a key fob to enter. The equipment is clean and quite complete. The space is small but well-planned. It wasn't too crowded in the evening. There are showers, lockers, and lockers. Lockers are first-come, first-served, and you have to lock them yourself; most people didn't lock them.

author: Marquez
text: Owner, please check. There's always a strong body odor on the 4th floor on weekend mornings. Because of that, if I want to go in the morning, I have to go to City Hall. The restrooms are dirty and there's no soap. The squat rack isn't always parallel to the mirror.
